modules.description: This module manages an in-memory key-value store with string keys and values, leveraging a hash table for efficient lookups and updates. It supports operations to load data from files, modify entries, and persist changes to disk, making it ideal for handling system identifiers like UUIDs and serial numbers that require durable storage and dynamic configuration. The ability to convert key-value lists to strings and synchronize with disk enables use cases such as bootstrapping system properties and maintaining runtime state across sessions.
